---
layout: layouts/base.njk
order: 0
eleventyNavigation: Home
title: Swiss Sovereign AI — Fine-Tuned Apertus, Run in Your Jurisdiction
description: sysf.io fine-tunes Apertus — Switzerland's open LLM from EPFL, ETH Zurich and CSCS — on your documents and runs it inside your infrastructure. Open weights your auditors can inspect, no US API in the loop, and you own the model.
faq:
  - q: What is sysf.io?
    a: sysf.io is a Swiss sovereign-AI engineering studio. We fine-tune Switzerland's open Apertus model on your data and ship it as a production system — retrieval, agents and guardrails wired to your systems, deployed in Swiss or EU jurisdiction, or fully on-premise. The result is a compliant, private, customized AI system you own — not a demo.
  - q: Which model do you use — is it always Apertus?
    a: Apertus is our foundation of choice — Switzerland's fully open, multilingual LLM from EPFL, ETH Zurich and CSCS, with open weights and documented training data, which is exactly what auditors and regulators want to see. But we're not dogmatic — we test open-weight models against an evaluation set built from your documents and deploy whichever wins. Apertus, Llama or Mistral — the evaluation decides, not the logo. All of them run fully inside your jurisdiction with weights you can inspect and own.
  - q: Does our data ever leave our environment?
    a: For Production and Air-gapped engagements — no. Training and inference run inside your tenancy or your datacentre, with no third-party LLM APIs and no data egress. Pilots run either in your environment or in a dedicated single-tenant Swiss cloud environment under a data-processing agreement, with all data and derived weights deleted or handed over to you at project end — your choice at scoping.
  - q: How is this "compliant by design"?
    a: Compliance is built into the architecture rather than bolted on. Open weights give you transparency and auditability; in-jurisdiction deployment addresses the Swiss Federal Act on Data Protection (FADP/nFADP) and EU GDPR; and documented data lineage plus guardrails support your EU AI Act obligations. We deliver the compliance and audit documentation alongside the model.
  - q: What does "end-to-end" mean here?
    a: We take a use case from data preparation and fine-tuning through evaluation, guardrails, deployment, monitoring and ongoing iteration. You get a maintained production system with agent orchestration, retrieval (RAG) and tools wired to your systems — plus a support and maintenance agreement — not a proof-of-concept that stalls.
  - q: How do we start?
    a: Engagements start with a fixed-scope Pilot on a single high-value use case — prove the numbers on your own data, then decide about production with an evaluation report in hand. Where needed, we take the system fully on-prem. Book a call and we'll scope it with you.
